        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 2 at 2:16AM CDT by NWS Tulsa OK</headline>
        <description>At 216 AM CDT, Doppler radar indicated a strong thunderstorm 5 miles
west of Midland, moving northeast at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down small tree limbs and blow
around unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation
is possible.

Locations in or near the path include...
Hackett...                        Arkola...
Huntington...                     Cameron...
Witcherville...                   Pocola...
Dayton...                         Poteau...
Midland...                        Bonanza...
Jenson...                         Excelsior...
Hartford...                       Burnville...
Rock Island...                    Greenwood...
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 700 AM CDT for
southeastern Oklahoma.</instruction>
